    "plan_cost_usd": 0.7293365500000001,
    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\nHere's what will be built — **only 2 new files + 2 small registry edits, no existing components touched**:\n\n---\n\n### New files\n\n**1. `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx`**\n\n7 named exports using the same **two-context pattern** as `carousel.tsx`:\n\n| Export | Element | Key behavior |\n|---|---|---|\n| `Stepper` | `<div>` | Root; provides `StepperContext` with `activeStep` + `orientation` |\n| `StepperItem` | `<div>` | Derives `\"completed\" \\| \"active\" \\| \"pending\"` state; provides `StepperItemContext` |\n| `StepperTrigger` | `<button>` | Shows step number by default; styled (border/filled/muted) by state |\n| `StepperTitle` | `<p>` | `text-sm font-medium` |\n| `StepperDescription` | `<p>` | `text-sm text-muted-foreground` |\n| `StepperSeparator` | `<div>` | Placed **inside** `StepperItem` to read its context; `bg-primary` when step is completed, `bg-border` otherwise |\n| `StepperContent` | `<div>` | Returns `null` unless `step === activeStep` |\n\n**2. `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx`**\n\n3-step \"Account → Profile → Complete\" demo with `useState`, clickable triggers, per-step content panels, and Next/Previous buttons.\n\n---\n\n### Registry edits\n\n- **`ui/_registry.ts`**: Insert `stepper` entry between `spinner` and `switch` (alphabetical order, no `dependencies` needed — pure React + `@/lib/utils`)\n- **`examples/_registry.ts`**: Insert `stepper-demo` entry between `spinner-item` and `switch-demo` with `registryDependencies: [\"stepper\", \"button\"]`\n\n---\n\n### Key design decision: separator placement\n\n`StepperSeparator` is placed **inside** `<StepperItem>` in JSX (not as a sibling between items). This gives it access to `StepperItemContext` without needing a `step` prop — the same way `CarouselItem` owns its own padding. In the demo, users wrap `<StepperTrigger />` + `<StepperSeparator />` in an inner `<div className=\"flex items-center\">` to achieve the horizontal circle→line layout.",
